text.section:
When the commission acquires or makes available to any district the equipment or infrastructure above referred to, it shall require said district to fully amortize, in the form of rentals or payments, to the Division of Conservation, as referred to in KRS Chapter 146, any amount so expended by the commission for such assistance. The amount and method of amortization for each piece of heavy equipment or infrastructure shall be determined by the commission, subject to approval of the commissioner of natural resources. The amount and method of amortization for each piece of heavy or specialized equipment shall be determined on the basis of a rental to be charged by the district to the user of equipment sufficient to:
Fully amortize to the division the capital outlay for the machinery itself over the period of its reasonably anticipated full usefulness;
Cover the cost of operation, maintenance and repairs;
Pay the usual cost of providing an operator; and
Compensate the district for the usual costs of transportation from one (1) job to another.
